First brought to notice by Master in 1867, who sent the plates to the Madras Government. Described and translated (but not edited) by T. Foulkes (

          ). First edited (probably from estampages) by A. C. Burnell (

            137-138
            27
          ) with a lithograph (of an inked estampage?) in Plate 27. Re-edited by J. F. Fleet (

          ) by which time the plates had been lost, so Fleet worked from Burnell's lithograph. PEM's record says Fleet's edition includes a facsimile, but this does not seem to be the case; CHECK a printed copy of IA20. The present edition by Dániel Balogh is based on a collation of the above editions with the estampages published by Burnell.
